The police’s Lungelo Dlamini says both officers were wounded, while the criminals ran away. JOHANNESBURG - Police are searching for the criminals responsible for shooting two officers in Tembisa, Johannesburg. It’s understood the police officers were on patrol earlier on Thursday when a vehicle stopped close by. Two gunmen got out of the car and opened fire. The police’s Lungelo Dlamini says both officers were wounded, while the criminals ran away. “Police impounded a vehicle during the investigation. We’re also appealing to the members of the community who might information that can assist us to contact Crimestop.”